	Charlize for apes    
	 London, Oct. 4 (PTI): Actress Charlize Theron has taken up the cause of African apes after meeting primatologist Jane Goodall, 76, during the filming of the TV series Iconoclasts.      
	Theron 35, met Goodall at the Tchimpounga sanctuary, in the Republic of Congo, Africa, where the primatologist and her staff look after orphaned chimpanzees rescued from poachers.      
	The actress was introduced to juvenile chimps as she and Goodall discussed the issues that face Africas young people and its wildlife, reports the Daily Mail.    
	Marilyn life    
	 London (PTI): Actress Marilyn Monroes pleas to end her life in the years leading up to her tragic death have been exposed in a new book. Named Fragments, it features excerpts from diaries, notes and letters of Monroe left to her mentor Lee Strasberg.
                                                                                                                                                      
